Plug-in name: Alias Analysis
Plug-in shortname: alias
Description: Lightweight May-Alias Analysis (experimental)

Most options of the form '-alias-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-alias-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-alias              Enable May-Alias Analyzer (opposite option is -no-alias)
-alias-debug-table  switch to debug mode when printing statement or function
                    tables (with options -alias-show-stmt-table and
                    -alias-show-function-table) (opposite option is
                    -alias-no-debug-table)
-alias-dot-output <f>  output final abstract state as dot file <f>
                    (preferably use -alias-dot-output="f")
-alias-show-function-table  display summary for each function after the
                    analysis (opposite option is
                    -alias-no-show-function-table)
-alias-show-stmt-table  display abstract state for each statement after the
                    analysis (opposite option is -alias-no-show-stmt-table)

*** DEBUG

-alias-debug <n>    level of debug for plug-in Alias Analysis (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-alias-help         help of plug-in Alias Analysis
-alias-h            alias for option -alias-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-alias-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Alias Analysis to a file.
                    <K> is a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -alias-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-alias-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -alias-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -alias-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-alias-verbose <n>  level of verbosity for plug-in Alias Analysis (default to
                    1)
-alias-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category <k1>
                    to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -alias-warn-key help to get
                    a list of available categories, and * to enable all
                    categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -alias-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
